2023: sleep more. Shout out to all of the parents who will do whatever it takes for some sleep. Do whatever works for you, don’t compare your family to someone else’s. Do I want my child’s bed in our bedroom?? No I don’t, but we will do what it takes for sleep and to make our child comfortable! (Insert, amen)

Society tends to talk about how sleep deprived you will be with your newborn, but society should mention you can be JUST AS sleep deprived with your 12 month old, 18 month old, and potentially your 2-3 year old. 

I remember when tanner was 3 and Winnie was 18 months and both of them wanted to sleep in our bed, it was daunting! It felt like every night we were preparing for battle. We did what worked for us in that season of life and we pulled through, just like we always do. So if you are struggling around sleep time with your littles, just know it’s not forever and do whatever works for you. If your child goes to bed easy and sleeps through the night, you are one of the lucky ones ❤️

How often do we just move past our resolutions without holding ourselves accountable? Resolutions or goals don’t have to even look like loose weight, get promoted, cure world hunger, (although that would be epic) one of mine this year was simply to soak up more sun and spend more time in our sunroom. So far my resolution is working out nicely, I put a small treadmill in here and got a new olive tree named, Ollie, thanks to @theolivetreebox and all is good in our home. Another resolution of mine was to take a bath and do more skin care routine once a week. A small baby step towards self care for this mama of 3. Hope this shows someone change doesn’t have to be grand to be useful. ❤️✨ would love to hear your thoughts and how your goals are going for 2023!

“Two Little Shadows”
I saw a young mother
With eyes full of laughter
And two little shadows
Came following after.
 
Wherever she moved,
They were always right there
Holding onto her skirts,
Hanging onto her chair.
Before her, behind her -
An adhesive pair.
 
‘Don’t you ever get weary
As, day after day,
your two little tagalongs
Get in your way? ’
 
She smiled as she shook
Her pretty young head,
And I’ll always remember
The words that she said.
 
‘It’s good to have shadows
That run when you run,
That laugh when you’re happy
And hum when you hum -
For you only have shadows
 
When your life’s filled with sun.’

Giant strawberry pop-tart to kick off the holiday weekend 🇺🇸🍓🎆

For this recipe and you could use premade pie crust or puff pastry. Simmer a handful of strawberries with some strawberry preserves or jelly on low until strawberries are slightly chunky. Place strawberry filling on crust and then place the second crust on top and pinch down edges with fingers. I like to run my finger under water for a better seal or use fork to seal edges more. Follow pre made crust cooking instructions. (I cooked mine on 425 for about 15 mins) Frosting- 4 oz cream cheese, 1 cup powder sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla, half stick of soft butter- beat together.

These are bananas, cut in half, and placed on a popsicle stick. Dipped in vanilla yogurt, and topped with chocolate chips and sprinkles (can add whatever!) and froze for 3+ hours! These will also be a perfect after school treat! Can’t believe these kids will be back in school in less than 2 weeks!

If you have any tips for long flights with kids or international travel, drop them below or slide into my DMs 🩶
Postcard no. 1, with love from Barcelona📮
Postcard no. 2- Barcelona y Valencia 🇪🇸 <3-the Coldings
Postcard no. 3- The Italian Riviera and Ibiza felt like a dream🛥️ 🛟

Wow, I am not sure how to put this trip and these places into words. The copious history, artifacts, surreal views, the food, the people, sharing this trip with my husband, kids, and parents- it has been a dream that I am not taking for granted given the current circumstances of this world. So many people are suffering at the hands of evil and that is not lost on us. Grateful for the last 2 weeks together even through the stresses of traveling with 3 young children, we are grateful!

The one where mom stuffs her own stocking …
